# shadcn/ui (shared components)

Use primitives from `@/components/ui` — **not** raw `<button>`, `<input>`, or one-off styled HTML for standard UI.

```tsx
// ✅ GOOD
import { Button, Input, Alert, Card, Label } from "@/components/ui";
import { toast } from "sonner";

// ✅ Also fine (tree-shaking)
import { Button } from "@/components/ui/button";

// ❌ BAD — ad-hoc UI for standard controls
<button className="px-4 py-2 bg-blue-500">Submit</button>
```

## Rules

- **Buttons:** `Button` with `variant` / `size` (`default`, `outline`, `destructive`, `ghost`, `link`)
- **Forms:** `Input`, `Textarea`, `Label`, `Field`, `Select`, `Checkbox` — pair with `Label` + `htmlFor`
- **Feedback:** `Alert`, `AlertDialog`, `toast` from `sonner` (Toaster already in layout)
- **Layout:** `Card`, `Separator`, `Sheet`, `Dialog`, `Tabs`, `Skeleton` for loading
- **New components:** `npx shadcn@latest add <name>` — do not copy-paste from old `client/` Bootstrap/raw HTML
- **Styling:** Tailwind + `cn()` from `@/lib/utils`; theme tokens in `src/app/globals.css`
- **Icons:** `lucide-react` (shadcn default), not mixed icon sets for new UI unless existing page already uses `react-icons`

Legacy `styled-components` in `src/components/products/` may remain temporarily; **new or refactored UI** should use shadcn.
